.TH "__pci_register_driver" 9 "__pci_register_driver" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__pci_register_driver \- register a new pci driver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __pci_register_driver
.BI "(struct pci_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "struct module *owner "  ","
.BI "const char *mod_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
the driver structure to register
.IP "owner" 12
owner module of drv
.IP "mod_name" 12
module name string
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Adds the driver structure to the list of registered drivers.
Returns a negative value on error, otherwise 0.
If no error occurred, the driver remains registered even if
no device was claimed during registration.
